CNCP v1 24685
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#3950: Nested elements in kept alive component are replaced before the transition",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:27:34.637204+00:00",
  "text": "Nested elements in kept alive component are replaced before the transition\n\n### Version\r\n3.1.1\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[Playground](https://sfc.vuejs.org/#)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n1. Click on toggle multiple times\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nIt should transition from Foo Foo to Bar Bar and vice versa\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nIt transitions from Foo Bar to Bar Bar and then Bar Foo Foo Foo\r\n\r\n---\r\n- Simplified from https://github.com/vuejs/vue-router-next/issues/983\r\n- Removing KeepAlive fixes the problem\r\n- This behavior is different from Vue 2\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":lady_beetle:  bug",
    "scope: transition",
    "scope: keep-alive"
  ],
